pygpc.testfunctions.wing_weight module¶

pygpc.testfunctions.wing_weight.wing_weight(x)[source]¶

10-dimensional test function which models a light aircraft wing

Forrester, A., Sobester, A., & Keane, A. (2008). Engineering design via surrogate modelling: a practical guide. Wiley.

y = wing_weight(x)

Input:
x … input data [N_input x 10]
x1(Sw) ∈ [150, 200] x2(Wfw) ∈ [220, 300] x3(A) ∈ [6, 10] x4(Λ) ∈ [-10, 10] x5(q) ∈ [16, 45] x6(λ) ∈ [0.5, 1] x7(tc) ∈ [0.08, 0.18] x8(Nz) ∈ [2.5, 6] x9(Wdg) ∈ [1700, 2500] x10(Wp) ∈ [0.025, 0.08]
Output:
y … result [N_input x 1]
